cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with the use of machine learning algorithms for medical image analysis, specifically for pulmonary nodule detection in chest radiographs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning method, which involves active learning and data mining, indicating that it could also fit into the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of pseudo-negative labels from unlabeled data suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the extraction of relevant information from large datasets. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could also place it in the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
